    <h3> To create a 3D model in Blender, I primarily needed a mix of 
        technical software proficiency and artistic foundational skills. According 
        to me, key skills is 3D navigation and an understanding of topology to ensure 
         clean, efficient models. On the tool side, the most essential for any modeler are
          transformations (Move, Rotate, Scale) and core editing functions like Extrude 
          (E), Inset (I), Bevel (Ctrl+B), and Loop Cut (Ctrl+R). Additionally, 
          using Modifiers, such as Mirror or Subdivision Surface which allows for
           non-destructive modeling, while hardware like a 3-button mouse 
           and a mid-grade PC with a dedicated graphics card 
            are necessary to run the software smoothly. </h3><hr>


